{"word":"G4596 - σηρικός - sērikós - say-ree-kos' - Silk","sections":[{"paragraph":"<strong>மூல வார்த்தை / Original: </strong><span class=\"hebrewOrGreek\">σηρικός</span>"},{"paragraph":"<strong>எழுத்துமாற்றம் / Transliteration: </strong><span class=\"transliteration\">sērikós</span>"},{"paragraph":"<strong>ஒலிபெயர்ப்பு / Phonetic: </strong><span class=\"phonetic\">say-ree-kos'</span>"},{"paragraph":"<strong>சுருக்க விளக்கம் / Short Definition: </strong><span class=\"short-definition\">Silk</span>"},{"paragraph":"<span class=\"parts-of-speech\"><strong>இலக்கண சொல்வகை / Part(s) of speech: </strong>Adjective / பெயரடை</span>"},{"paragraph":"பட்டாடை - பெயரடை"},{"paragraph":"silken"},{"paragraph":"<span class=\"original-in-english\"><strong>ஆங்கில மூலம் / Original in English: </strong>From <b>&#x03A3;&#x03B7;&#x0301;&#x03C1;</b> <b>Se&#x0304;r</b> (an Indian tribe from whom <i>silk</i> was procured; hence the name of the <i>silkworm</i>); <i>Seric</i>, that is, <i>silken</i> (neuter as noun, a <i>silky</i> fabric): - silk.</span>"},{"paragraph":""}]}